{{Infobox company | name = Brainbench | logo = Brainbench logo.png | logo_size = 200px | caption = The Brainbench logo | image = | type = Subsidiary | services = Online testing and certifications | foundation = 1998 | location = USA | industry = Testing in [[information Technology]] and other fields | parent = SHL | homepage = {{url|http://www.brainbench.com}} }}
'''Brainbench''' is an [[online education]] company founded in January 1998 (until 8 December 1999 the name was '''Tekmetrics.com'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/brainbench|title=Predicting Employee Success |publisher=Brainbench |date=1999-12-08 |accessdate=2012-06-14}}</ref>) and later acquired by PreVisor in 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ethicalbusinessbureau.com/Brainbench/ |title=Brainbench - Free Online Skills & Certification Testings at Brainbench |publisher=Ethicalbusinessbureau.com |date=2009-05-07 |accessdate=2012-06-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130730074730/http://ethicalbusinessbureau.com/Brainbench/# |archive-date=30 July 2013 |dead-url=yes |df=dmy-all }}</ref> PreVisor merged with SHL in 2011; SHL was acquired by the [[CEB Inc.|Corporate Executive Board]] in 2012.<ref>[http://www.xcelerationpartners.com/index.php/ct-menu-item-13 History - Xceleration Partners]</ref> CEB was acquired by [[Gartner]] in 2017.<ref>[http://fortune.com/2017/01/05/gartner-buys-ceb/ IT Research Firm Gartner Is Buying CEB for $2.6 Billion Billion]</ref> CEB's Talent Assessment business was acquired from Gartner by Exponent Private Equity in 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gartner.com/newsroom/id/3852963|title=Gartner Signs Definitive Agreement to Sell CEB Talent Assessment to Exponent for $400 Million|access-date=2018-07-11|language=en}}</ref> The CEB Talent Assessment Business was re-branded as SHL in 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.shl.com/en/newsroom/press-releases/the-leading-provider-of-talent-assessments-shl-is-reinvented/|title=The Leading Provider of Talent Assessments, SHL is Reinvented - SHL|work=SHL|access-date=2018-07-11|language=en-US}}</ref> Brainbench provides online certifications mainly in the [[Information Technology]] field and others in general.<ref> {{cite journal | title = Examining the value of Brainbench certifications | last = Davis | first = David | journal = [[TechRepublic]] | date = August 20, 2001 | url = http://articles.techrepublic.com.com/5100-10878_11-1031193.html | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100327213653/http://articles.techrepublic.com.com/5100-10878_11-1031193.html | archive-date=27 March 2010 | accessdate = July 30, 2016 }}</ref><ref> {{cite journal | title = Testing the limits | last = Raths | first = David | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=tRkEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA44&dq=%22Brainbench%22+-inpublisher:icon&as_brr=0&cd=1#v=onepage&q=%22Brainbench%22%20-inpublisher%3Aicon&f=false | journal = NetworkWorld | date = August 20, 2001 | accessdate = July 30, 2016 }}</ref><ref> {{cite journal | title = Certifiably Interested: Thompson Invests in Brainbench | last = Mark | first = Roy | journal = Internetnews.com | date = August 8, 2000 | url = http://www.internetnews.com/bus-news/article.php/432391 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110604035152/http://www.internetnews.com/bus-news/article.php/432391 | archive-date=4 June 2011 | accessdate = July 30, 2016 }}</ref><ref> {{cite journal | title = IT Certification Moves to Intranets | last = Swanson | first = Sandra | journal = InformationWeek | date = July 17, 2000 | url = http://www.informationweek.com/795/brainbench.htm | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110612021040/http://www.informationweek.com/795/brainbench.htm | archive-date=12 June 2011 | accessdate = July 30, 2016}}</ref><ref> {{cite journal | title = Online Assessment Gets Good Marks from Faculty, Students | last = Santovec | first = Mary Lou | journal = Distance Education Report | page = 4 | date = September 1, 2002 | url = http://qmconference2011.pbworks.com/w/file/fetch/47722444/0209DERA.pdf | accessdate = July 30, 2016 }}</ref> The company has provided its services to over 5,000 corporate clients and over 6&nbsp;million individuals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brainbench.com/xml/bb/business/aboutus/aboutus.xml |title=Employment Testing - About Us |publisher=Brainbench |date= |accessdate=2012-06-14}}</ref> Some of Brainbench's 630 exams are available free of charge, while others are administered for a fee.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://certification.about.com/od/certifications/p/brainbench.htm |title=Brainbench Certifications |publisher=Certification.about.com |date=2009-03-26 |accessdate=2012-06-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050515092755/http://certification.about.com/od/certifications/p/brainbench.htm# |archive-date=15 May 2005 |dead-url=yes |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
==Testing== Brainbench provides online tests for registered users on its website. The tests include paid tests, which require payment in order to take the exams, free tests, and beta tests, which are pre-released tests where no certificates are provided when testing is completed.<ref name="CCIE 2001">{{cite web | author=Davis, David | title=Examining the value of Brainbench certifications | website=TechRepublic | date=August 20, 2001 | url=http://www.techrepublic.com/article/examining-the-value-of-brainbench-certifications/ | accessdate=August 27, 2016}}</ref>
