'''FPCT Tumaini Secondary School''',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tumainisec.blogspot.com/|title=FPCT TUMAINI SECONDARY SCHOOL|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> is the private school located in the Southern part of [[Tanzania]] in [[Katavi Region|Katavi]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.katavi.go.tz/|title=Tovuti ya Mkoa wa Katavi|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> region, formerly [[Rukwa Region|Rukwa]] Region.
{{Infobox school | name = | motto = Fear for the Lord is the Beginning of Knowledge | motto_translation = Kumcha Bwana ni chanzo cha Maarifa | streetaddress = Mpanda, Katavi | city = Nduwi Katumba | religious_affiliation = FPCT Katumba Main Polish | founded = 2005 | headmaster = Gustave Sedekia (Ag.) }}
The school was established in 2006 by the Free [[Pentecostalism|Pentecostal Church of Tanzania]] under the Manager, archbishop of the Parish Rev. Jonathan Kidebuye. The school now serves large number of population in [[Tanzania]] especially people from Lake zone regions: [[Mwanza Region|Mwanza]], [[Shinyanga Region|Shinyanga]], [[Bariadi]], [[Kagera Region|Kagera]], and Mara, central zone regions of [[Tabora]], [[Dodoma]] and [[Singida Region|Singida]]. It is accommodates a large number of people from the Southern zone Regions of [[Tanzania]]. The school is about 31 Kilometers from [[Katavi Region|Katavi]] capital Town of [[Mpanda]].
== School Motto ==
The [[Motto]] of the school is [[Fear]] for the Lord is the Beginning of the Knowledge (Kumcha Bwana ni chanzo cha Maarifa), the [[school]] other than preparing the students academically it as well prepares them spiritually, every [[student]] based on his/her [[religion]].
