'''Giuseppe Ciccimarra''' (22 May 1790 &ndash; 5 December 1836) was an Italian [[tenor]], closely associated with [[Gioachino Rossini|Rossini]] roles.
==Career== Ciccimarra was born in [[Altamura]]. He was considered one of the best [[comprimario]] tenors of his time.
For Rossini, he created, at the [[Teatro San Carlo]] in Naples, several roles including: Iago in ''[[Otello (Rossini)|Otello]]'', Goffredo in ''[[Armida (Rossini)|Armida]]'', Aronne in ''[[Mosè in Egitto]]'', Ernesto in ''[[Ricciardo e Zoraide]]'', Pilade in ''[[Ermione]]'', Condulmiero in ''[[Maometto II]]''.
He retired from the stage in 1826, and taught voice and piano in Vienna. Among his pupils were [[Josef Tichatschek]], creator of Wagner's ''[[Rienzi]]'' and ''[[Tannhäuser (opera)|Tannhäuser]]'', the Austrian tenor [[Heinrich Kreutzer]] and [[Sophie Löwe]], one of the most famous opera singers of her time. He died in Venice.
== Sources == * Roland Mancini and Jean-Jacques Rouveroux (orig. H. Rosenthal and J. Warrack, French edition), ''Guide de l’opéra'', Les indispensables de la musique ([[Fayard]], 1995). {{ISBN|2-213-59567-4}}
