The '''Innogen Institute''' is a collaboration between the [[University of Edinburgh]] [[University of Edinburgh School of Social and Political Sciences|School of Social and Political Sciences]] and the [[Open University]] that explores the social and economic impact of innovation in the [[life sciences]] and [[genomics]].  It was founded in 2013.<ref name=innogen>{{cite web|title=About Innogen|url=http://www.innogen.ac.uk/about/|publisher=innogen|accessdate=29 January 2014}}</ref>

