{{Unreferenced|date=December 2008}} {{Infobox University |name = Kirir Women's University of Science and Technology |established = May 2002 |type = [[Private University|Women's]] |city = [[Nairobi]] |country = [[Kenya]] |campus = Kasarani, Westlands / Muguga Green |website= [http://www.kwust.ac.ke/ www.kwust.ac.ke]}}
'''Kiriri Women's University of Science and Technology''', often referred to as KWUST, is a non-state funded secular women's [[university]] in [[Nairobi]], [[Kenya]]. Its aim is to empower women in sciences. Kiriri Women's University is the only women's university in east and southern Africa.
It offers B.Science degrees in mathematics (actuarial, pure, statistics), computer science and business administration, as well as diplomas and certificates.
Admission is in May and September every year.
