{{Infobox company | name = Mandhu College | logo = | type = [[Education]] | key_people = Ibrahim Ismail, [[Chairman]] | foundation = 1998 | location = [[Male']], [[Maldives]] | homepage = {{URL|http://www.mandhucollege.edu.mv}} }}
'''Mandhu College''' (formerly '''Mandhu Learning Centre''') is a [[Private university|private college]] providing Higher [[Education in the Maldives]]. Mandhu College collaborates with universities in UK and Australia to provide accredited tertiary courses locally.
The Mandhu Learning Centre was established in 1998, and later inaugurated as the Mandhu College in December 2009.<ref>[http://www.miadhu.com/2009/12/local-news/president-inaugurates-mandhu-college/ "President inaugurates Mandhu College". Retrieved April 18, 2011.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120316152725/http://www.miadhu.com/2009/12/local-news/president-inaugurates-mandhu-college/ |date=March 16, 2012 }}</ref> The courses taught at Mandhu College are accredited by the Maldives Qualifications Authority.
