{{notability|Products|date=July 2016}} {{Infobox software | name = XBlock | title = | logo = EdX Logo.PNG | screenshot = | caption = | collapsible = | author = | developer = | released = {{Release date|2013|03|14}}<!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} --> | discontinued = | latest release version = | latest release date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} --> | latest preview version = 0.1 (pre-alpha) | latest preview date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} --> | programming language = [[Python (programming language)|Python2]] | platform = | size = | language = [[English language|English]] | genre = [[Course management system]] | license = [[GNU Affero General Public License]] | repo = {{URL|https://github.com/edX/XBlock}} }}
'''XBlock''' is the [[Software development kit|SDK]] for the [[edX]] [[Massive open online course|MOOC]] platform, written in Python2, and announced and released publicly on March 14, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marketwatch.com/story/edx-takes-first-step-toward-open-source-vision-by-releasing-xblock-sdk-2013-03-14 |title=edX Takes First Step toward Open Source Vision by Releasing XBlock SDK |publisher=MarketWatch |date= |accessdate=2013-08-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Nelson |first=Sharleen |url=http://campustechnology.com/articles/2013/03/14/edx-releases-open-source-tool-for-building-interactive-mooc-courseware.aspx?admgarea=news |title=EdX Releases Open Source Tool For Building Interactive MOOC Courseware |publisher=Campus Technology |date= |accessdate=2013-08-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.technapex.com/2013/03/edx-opens-up-online-learning-platform-releases-source-code/ |title=EdX Opens Up Online Learning Platform, Releases Source Code |publisher=Technapex |date=2013-03-19 |accessdate=2013-08-25}}</ref> It aims to enable the global software development community to participate in the construction of the edX educational platform and the next generation of online and blended courses.
==Documentation== Documentation for the XBlock SDK is currently in an ″extremely preliminary″ state, and developers are encouraged to communicate directly and interactively with the XBlock authors before proceeding to build something new with it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://xblock.readthedocs.org/en/latest/ |title=XBlock — XBlock 0.1 documentation |publisher=Xblock.readthedocs.org |date= |accessdate=2013-08-25}}</ref>
